# Session Memory — Walkthrough

## What Was Built

**Layer 13 — Controlled Session Memory** per §2.13. Provides statefulness via caching previous interactions using a strict context boundary.

## Architecture

Memory sits between the Orchestrator and the API Gateway. To aggressively prevent LLM halluciation spiraling, we use Pydantic schemas as a "firewall" to strip intermediate trace buffers before serializing to Redis.

**Data Flow:**
```mermaid
graph LR
    SUB["Orchestrator Payload<br/>(Contains Raw Reasoning)"] --> DTO["MemoryInteraction"]
    DTO -->|Drops reasoning_trace| VALID["Validated Dump"]
    VALID --> REDIS["redis.asyncio.set()"]
```

